title: Arrests continue in wake of shootout at ‘Stop the Violence’ event
content:
AVON PARK — Deputies have collared another suspect in the May 14 shootout at a “Stop the Violence” event in Avon Park.
Avontra Treon Moore, 22, of Lake Placid, was arrested Thursday afternoon (May 19) — four days after the early evening shootout that injured a 5-year-old boy and a 20-year-old woman.
